The paper deals with clone detection, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). It specifically focuses on detecting clones across different programming languages, which involves analyzing the syntax and semantics of code (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of static and dynamic analysis techniques, which are common in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The authors use machine learning techniques to cluster similar code snippets, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of their work in language migration tools, which is related to software development (cs.SD).
